  "local_port": 46236,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is mail signature?",
  "response": "A **mail signature** (or **email signature**) is a block of text, graphics, or contact information automatically appended to the end of an email message. It serves as a digital business card or personal identifier, providing recipients with essential details about the sender. A well-crafted signature can add professionalism and credibility to your emails while making it easier for recipients to get in touch with you.\n\n### Common elements of an email signature include:\n1. **Name**: Full name or business name.\n2. **Job Title**: Position within the organization.\n3. **Company**: Name of the company or organization.\n4. **Contact Information**: Phone number, email address, or secondary contact details.\n5. **Website**: Link to a personal or company website.\n6. **Social Media Links**: Links to LinkedIn, Twitter, Facebook, or other professional profiles.\n7. **Logo or Image**: Company logo or a professional headshot.\n8. **Disclaimer or Legal Notice**: Required for certain industries (e.g., confidentiality notices).\n9. **Call to Action**: Invitations to schedule a meeting, join a webinar, or visit a landing page.\n10. **Design Elements**: Lines, icons, or formatting to make the signature visually appealing.\n\n### Example of a professional email signature:\n```\nJane Doe  \nMarketing Manager  \nABC Corporation  \nPhone: +1 (123) 456-7890  \nEmail: jane.doe@abccorp.com  \nWebsite: www.abccorp.com  \n\n[LinkedIn Logo] [Twitter Logo]  \nConnect with me on LinkedIn | Follow me on Twitter  \n\nConfidentiality Notice: This email and any attachments are confidential and intended solely for the recipient.  \n```\n\n### Tips for creating an effective email signature:\n- Keep it concise and avoid clutter.\n- Use a professional font and consistent formatting.\n- Ensure it looks good on both desktop and mobile devices.\n- Avoid including too many images or links that may trigger spam filters.\n- Update it regularly to reflect any changes in your contact information or role.\n\nEmail signatures are a simple yet powerful way to leave a lasting impression and maintain professionalism in your communications.",
